fields.description:
As a cloud user I would like to be able to use multiple network interfaces with EC2 VPC instances so that I can access multiple subnets (vpcs)

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-resource-ec2-network-interface-attachment.html

comments.body:
Restored/tested support for AWS::EC2::NetworkInterfaceAttachment resource.

This fix will be updated and merged to master once pending framework changes to cloudformation for stack updates are completed.

Commit (in branch for review):
https://github.com/sjones4/eucalyptus/commit/65b8d0b05648665c46e923d21d9dcff3802cad94
The attached template can be used to test network interface attachment.

Is there a complete list of resources we started supporting in 4.3? This is the 2nd one I've noticed that was on my "unsupported" list in the console and being flagged when people import templates. I'd like to be sure I remove all of the newly supported resources and properties. (cc: [~ethomas])

[~dkavanagh], I don't think there is a 4.3 list of resources, some 4.3 changes are documented here:

https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/wiki/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=119832584

this filter will show all the stories, new features, and improvements for cloudformation in 4.3:

https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/issues/?filter=27700

*Eucalyptus Version*

{{4.3.0-0.25026.353.20160711git783d0ca.el7}}
